@@LoadImageListFromBitmap@TCustomImageList@TBitmap@TBitmap
<TITLE LoadImageListFromBitmap function>
 
Summary
  Loads the bitmaps for the ImageList from a bitmap.
 
Description
  The given bitmap is splitted into smaller bitmaps which are added to the image list. The mask   
bitmap is used as mask. Or the mask color is used if AutoMaskColor is false. Otherwise bottom left 
pixel's color is used as mask color.
 
Parameters
  ImgList       - The image list to which the splitted bitmap should be added Bitmap        - The  
bitmap that should be added to the image list MaskBitmap    - The bitmap mask that is used for the 
bitmap MaskColor     - Mask color (default: clFuchsia) AutoMaskColor - Set this to true if the mask 
color should be the bottom left pixel of each bitmap slice.
 
Return value
  The return value is the number of added bitmaps.
 
